# Meta Title Auto-Generation

To reduce redundancy and confusion in the CMS, meta titles are now auto-generated from hero titles instead of requiring separate fields.

## The Problem

Previously, we had three confusing title fields:
- **Page Title**: Redundant internal reference
- **Meta Title**: SEO title for browser tabs/search
- **Hero Title**: Visible content on the page

This created confusion and redundancy.

## The Solution

Now we use a cleaner approach:

1. **Hero Title**: Primary visible content (e.g., "My Projects")
2. **Auto-Generated Meta Title**: SEO title (e.g., "My Projects - Harrison Callahan")
3. **Route/Slug**: Programmatic references (e.g., `/projects`)

## Implementation

### CMS Schema
- Removed `metaTitle` field from base page schema
- Meta titles are always auto-generated from hero titles
- No more manual meta title fields to maintain

### Content Files
```json
{
  "hero": {
    "title": "My Projects",
    "subtitle": "Showcasing my work across different domains"
  }
  // metaTitle is auto-generated as "My Projects - Harrison Callahan"
}
```

### Page Components
```typescript
// Auto-generate meta title from hero title
function generateMetaTitle(heroTitle: string): string {
  return `${heroTitle} - Harrison Callahan`;
}

const metaTitle = generateMetaTitle(projectsPage.data.hero.title);
```

## Benefits

✅ **Less Confusion**: Only one primary title field (hero title)
✅ **Consistent SEO**: Auto-generated meta titles follow the same pattern
✅ **Reduced Redundancy**: No duplicate title fields
✅ **Better UX**: CMS is simpler and clearer
✅ **Maintainable**: Changes to hero titles automatically update SEO
✅ **Simplified Schema**: No more metaTitle fields to maintain

## Meta Title Generation

Meta titles are now always auto-generated from hero titles using the utility functions in `packages/core/src/utils/meta-title.ts`:

```typescript
// Core utility
generateMetaTitle("My Projects", "Harrison Callahan")
// "My Projects - Harrison Callahan"

// Site-specific utility
generatePortfolioMetaTitle("My Projects")
// "My Projects - Harrison Callahan"
```

## Utility Functions

Use the utility functions in `apps/cms/src/utils/meta-title.ts`:

- `generateMetaTitle(heroTitle, siteName)`: Generate meta title from hero title
- `generatePageMetaTitle(pageData, siteName)`: Generate meta title from page data with override support
